    <!-- Guide -->
    <string name="guide_section_tips">Tips</string>
    <string name="guide_tuner_desc">Detects the note you\'re playing in real time via the microphone. Shows the note name, cent deviation, and a visual indicator: green (in tune) or red (out of tune). Ideal for string, wind instruments or voice: check if you\'re playing the right note.</string>
    <string name="guide_metronome_desc">Digital metronome with BPM adjustable from 30 to 240, available time signatures (2/4, 3/4, 4/4, 6/8), visual beat indicators and Tap Tempo. Press the microphone button to activate the built-in tuner and check your intonation while playing in time.</string>
    <string name="guide_reference_desc">Generate a reference note for tuning or ear training. Quick A 440 Hz button, grid of 12 chromatic notes, and selectable octave from 2 to 7.</string>
    <string name="guide_practice_desc">The heart of the app. Load a note sequence (manual, photo scan, or MusicXML) and play them one by one. The app detects the note from the microphone and advances automatically. View the staff in Note, Context, Score, or Light mode. Use \"Hide\" to practice reading from the staff. Built-in metronome to play in time.</string>
    <string name="guide_exercises_desc">Ready-made exercises with progressive difficulty: Level 1 (basic notes C-G), Level 2 (complete scales), Level 3 (scales with accidentals and melodies), Level 4 (arpeggios and leaps).</string>
    <string name="guide_scales_desc">Generate scales and arpeggios in any key. Scales: Major, Minor, Harmonic, Melodic, Pentatonic, Chromatic. Arpeggios: Major, Minor, Diminished, Augmented, Seventh. Choose root note, octave, type and direction.</string>
    <string name="guide_scores_desc">Browse your MusicXML file library and practice directly from imported pieces.</string>
    <string name="guide_ear_training_desc">Train your musical ear: Recognize Note (guess the note you hear) and Recognize Interval (identify the interval between two notes). Three difficulty levels with 10 questions per session.</string>
    <string name="guide_challenge_desc">Test your speed and accuracy: choose source and time limit (30s, 1min, 2min) and play as many correct notes as possible. Each note is shown on the staff. Scoring system with accuracy bonus, speed bonus and combo multiplier.</string>
    <string name="guide_leaderboard_desc">Your top 20 challenge scores, with score, notes played, max combo and date.</string>
    <string name="guide_stats_desc">Overview of your progress: total sessions, practice time, best accuracy. Daily charts for accuracy, first attempt and reaction time.</string>
    <string name="guide_goals_desc">Set a goal (5, 10, 15 or 30 minutes per day), follow the circular progress, maintain your streak and view the calendar of the last 30 days. Time is tracked from all activities: practice, challenges and ear training.</string>
    <string name="guide_history_desc">Review all past sessions in a single chronological list: practice, ear training and challenges. Each type has a colored badge for easy identification. Tap a practice session to replay it.</string>
    <string name="guide_tip_quiet">Quiet environment: the app works best with little background noise.</string>
    <string name="guide_tip_distance">Microphone distance: keep the device 30-50 cm from your instrument.</string>
    <string name="guide_tip_daily">Daily practice: even 10 minutes a day makes a difference.</string>
    <string name="guide_tip_scales">Start with scales: mastering scales is the foundation for playing any piece.</string>
    <string name="guide_tip_ear">Regular ear training: even 5 minutes a day greatly improves your musical ear.</string>
